                    // Blog Post 7
                    a.anchor(name='7')
                    h3.ctitle Probation period for new employee
                    p
                        csmall Posted: February 1, 2017.
                        csmall2 By: Sergei Stadnik
                    br
                    p
                        img.img-responsive(src='img/blog/stick_figures.png')
                    br
                    p Reading time: 
                        strong 4 minutes
                    p The day when a new member becomes a part of the team and starts contributing is an exciting moment for this person. The newcomer typically  is very enthusiastic and anxious to add value. He / she has new ideas and views. It is critical to see how a prospective partner / teammate will fit in and able to work with the existing team.
